messages.author: dennis_jeffrey
messages.text:
On 2011/10/12 22:30:27, dyu1 wrote:
> 'format are' or did you mean 'formats are'?

The way you changed it is fine - and it was only a minor nit anyway ;-)

But FYI, I think even "format are" would have been grammatically correct here too, because the subject that the sentence is talking about is really the "server ports", and those are plural.  So it's the server ports that "are incorrect", not the "json format".
